   <mods:abstract>Has been so busy since return, unable to write letters to friends, but now
            will hopefully devote 1-2 hours a day to correspondence. Thanks for indignation about
            virulent publication against Jay "by an unworthy young man." Thanks also for drawing of
            machine for watering roads. Streets so encumbered by lumber for rebuilding burned houses
            that unlikely will water them any time soon. No public walks as yet; plan for planting
            the battery and ground near St. Paul√Üs church. Will gladly give son Benjamin journals to
            complete the lot. Letter from son Samuel about job in the mint; with current state of
            affairs probably would be delayed.</mods:abstract>
